The South African National Roads Agency Ltd (SANRAL) would like to notify travellers that temporary Stop and Go sections are scheduled for the N2 between Grahamstown and the Fish River Pass from Friday 21st July to Monday 2nd October.The Stop and Go s will be approximately 1.3km in length and will be installed on Section 13, between 79.5km and 92.6km, from 6.00am to 6:00pm.The expected delays will be approximately 15 minutes.Motorists are requested to plan their trips accordingly and be cautious when making use of the road. 